ckage and noting that package-private methods might be acceptable. There's a possibility of adjusting import order, which should start with static, followed by Java packages, then org, with a blank line after. I’m thinking about using AssertJ to assert that the stream is not null before the try-with-resources block. Interestingly, it seems that having a null resource in try-with-resources is okay and won't lead to a NullPointerException. However, if a dynamic resource is absent, the assertion might fail. I also want to check the Velocity version and consider whether we need to read components, although it seems unnecessary here. Adding a test to load through VelocityEngine could be a good idea to assert the runtime API. I'm aware that the dynamic-access site involves a call on line 48, and I’m making sure to follow the instructions about not compiling or running tests myself.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Clarifying file tracking and metadata**\\\\n\\\\nI’m considering whether to include the new file difference since it doesn't show due to untracked files. Using `git diff --no-index` might not be necessary, but I think a concise note would help clarify things. I should emphasize that I didn't run anything and mention that untracked metadata exists. Perhaps I should state, \\\\\\\"Note: metadata/... was already untracked; I did not touch it.\\\\\\\" Since it's not something we created, I want to ensure we avoid accidental changes to it, just to prevent any confusion.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Implemented focused coverage for `ContextClassLoaderResourceLoader`.\\n\\nChanges:\\n- Removed placeholder test:\\n  - `tests/src/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-velocity/1.1.7/src/test/java/org_codehaus_plexus/plexus_velocity/Plexus_velocityTest.java`\\n- Added dedicated dynamic-access test:\\n  - `tests/src/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-velocity/1.1.7/src/test/java/org_codehaus_plexus/plexus_velocity/ContextClassLoaderResourceLoaderTest.java`\\n- Added ordinary test resource:\\n  - `tests/src/org.codehaus.plexus/plexus-velocity/1.1.7/src/test/resources/templates/context-class-loader-resource-loader-template.vm`\\n\\nThe new test sets the thread context class loader, calls `ContextClassLoaderResourceLoader#getResourceStream`, and verifies the loaded resource content, which reaches the remaining uncovered `ClassLoader#getResourceAsStream(String)` call site.\\n\\nPer instruction, I did not run compilation or tests.\", \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0f86564dfe26fc150169ff878c70f881a38bdafcb5ab49d318\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 284, \"output\": 726, \"cacheRead\": 13312, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 14322, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 1778354046705, \"responseId\": \"resp_0f86564dfe26fc150169ff877f0d0081a3b782380e0ee0cce7\"}, \"toolResults\": []}\n\n===== /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge8/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/logs/org.codehaus.plexus:plexus-velocity:1.1.7/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-09T19-15-51-960127Z.log\n78:[tool-exec] end id=call_RonYV1dvLksbh5x2ivZVOjsx|fc_049667505a9e91930169ff87c3ba5c81a3ab89b77318e30b3a name=bash status=success\n101:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_start\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_RonYV1dvLksbh5x2ivZVOjsx|fc_049667505a9e91930169ff87c3ba5c81a3ab89b77318e30b3a\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge8/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2428-8b9c7e6e\\nAGENTS.md\\nbuild\\nbuild.gradle\\nbuild_spec.yaml\\ncheck-library-support.sh\\nci.json\\nCLAUDE.md\\nCOVERAGE.md\\ndocs\\nforge\\ngradle\\ngradle.properties\\ngradlew\\ngradlew.bat\\nLICENSE\\nmetadata\\nREADME.md\\nsettings.gra